An introduction to concepts, approaches and theories of clinical psychology. The course gives general framework for psychological explanations of development of disorders and interventions. Several disorders and therapies will be explained in detail at lectures, students are expected to go through independently the rest by textbook.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Acquisition of evidence-based approach to mental and behavioural disorders and psychological interventions. Teaching the ability to distinguish evidence-based approaches to mental disorders from conventional thinking.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1. Is familiar with basic principles and concepts of clinical psychology. 
2. Can differentiate the more essential mental and behavioural disorders.
3. Knows psychological models of mental and behavioural disorders. 
4. Is familiar with main therapeutic approaches. 
5. Knows ethical principles of psychologists.
